// EXPECTED BEHAVIOR:
// The parser should correctly track that `strip` is mutating `[tags]` and `[nested][field]`.
// It should recognize `[tags]` is an array or string, and `[nested][field]` is a string.
// Lineage for `[tags]` and `[nested][field]` should show a self-mutation (whitespace stripped).
// It should not raise errors on stripping arrays, as Logstash mutates all elements in an array.

filter {
  mutate {
    strip => ["tags", "[nested][field]"]
  }
}
